On 200 randomly sampled concepts with their top-2 negations [arnaoutcikm2022], in a crowdsourcing task where workers are asked about the accuracy and interestingness of given negative statements, UnCommonSense achieves a precision of 75% and a salience of 50%, while NegatER achieves a similar precision of 74% but lower salience of 29%.